  "response_text": "# Weekly Diet & Workout Routine\n\n## WORKOUT SCHEDULE\n\n**Monday: Upper Body Strength**\n- Warm-up: 5 min cardio\n- Bench press: 4×6-8 reps\n- Bent-over rows: 4×6-8 reps\n- Overhead press: 3×8-10 reps\n- Pull-ups/lat pulldowns: 3×8-10 reps\n- Bicep curls & tricep dips: 3×10-12 reps\n- Cool-down: stretching\n\n**Tuesday: Cardio & Core**\n- 30 min moderate cardio (running, cycling, rowing)\n- Planks: 3×45-60 sec\n- Russian twists: 3×20\n- Leg raises: 3×12-15\n\n**Wednesday: Lower Body Strength**\n- Warm-up: 5 min cardio\n- Squats: 4×6-8 reps\n- Deadlifts: 3×5-6 reps\n- Leg press: 3×8-10 reps\n- Leg curls: 3×10-12 reps\n- Calf raises: 3×12-15 reps\n\n**Thursday: Active Recovery**\n- 20-30 min light activity (yoga, walking, swimming)\n- Stretching & mobility work\n\n**Friday: Full Body & HIIT**\n- Warm-up: 5 min\n- Kettlebell swings: 3×15\n- Dumbbell thrusters: 3×12\n- Box jumps: 3×10\n- Burpees: 3×10\n- 15 min HIIT finisher\n\n**Saturday: Sports or Conditioning**\n- Pick an activity (basketball, hiking, CrossFit, etc.)\n- 45-60 minutes\n\n**Sunday: Complete Rest**\n- Light stretching only\n\n---\n\n## DAILY DIET PLAN\n\n### BREAKFAST (7-8 AM)\n- 3 whole eggs + 2 egg whites\n- 1 cup oatmeal with berries\n- 1 banana\n- Black coffee or green tea\n\n### SNACK 1 (10 AM)\n- Greek yogurt (150g)\n- Granola & honey\n- Almonds (small handful)\n\n### LUNCH (1 PM)\n- 150g grilled chicken/salmon\n- 1.5 cups brown rice or sweet potato\n- Mixed vegetables (broccoli, carrots)\n- Olive oil drizzle\n\n### SNACK 2 (4 PM)\n- Protein shake (25g protein powder)\n- 1 apple\n- Peanut butter (1 tbsp)\n\n### DINNER (7 PM)\n- 150g lean beef/turkey\n- 1 cup quinoa or pasta\n- Large salad with olive oil dressing\n- Steamed vegetables\n\n### OPTIONAL EVENING (if needed)\n- Casein protein shake or cottage cheese\n\n---\n\n## DAILY NUTRITION TARGETS\n- **Calories:** 2,200-2,500 (adjust based on goals)\n- **Protein:** 150-180g\n- **Carbs:** 250-300g\n- **Fats:** 60-75g\n\n---\n\n## TIPS FOR SUCCESS\n✓ Drink 3-4 liters of water daily  \n✓ Prep meals on Sunday  \n✓ Sleep 7-9 hours  \n✓ Adjust portions based on your goals  \n✓ Progressive overload in workouts  \n✓ Track your intake for 2-3 weeks  \n\n**Customize based on your fitness level, goals, and dietary preferences!**",
